                  </date>
               </dateline>
               <salute>W. Whitman</salute> 
            </opener>
            <p>
               <gap reason="illegible"/> sir</p>
            <p>On page 31 verse 2 line 3 of Drum Taps the word "recalls" is spelled "recals."  According to Webster &amp; Worcester it is wrong but before taking the responsibility of altering it, I wait for your decision.  Please let me know as soon as possible.  The other corrections and alterations <gap reason="deletion, illegible"/> 
               <del type="overstrike" status="unremarkable">I enclose a proof of 'O Pioneers!'" <unclear reason="illegible" resp="#hrb" cert="medium">&amp;</unclear> I think is improved</del>
            </p>
            <p>I enclose a bill showing the balance<gap reason="illegible"/>ount.  If I receive <gap reason="illegible"/> printing done by Saturday,<gap reason="illegible"/> you can transmit me the cost and I will deliver the <unclear reason="illegible" resp="#hrb" cert="low">texts</unclear> to your binder.</p>
            <closer rend="right">
               <salute>Your Respectfully,</salute>
               <signed>P. Eckler</signed>
            </closer>
         </div1>
         
